{"title_page": "Yeh Raat Phir Na Aayegi (1966 film)", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|Films|date=October 2015}}\n{{More citations needed|date=June 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{infobox film\n| name              = Yeh Raat Phir Na Aayegi<br> \u092f\u0939 \u0930\u093e\u0924 \u092b\u093f\u0930 \u0928 \u0906\u090f\u0917\u0940\n| director          = [[Brij]]\n| starring          = [[Sharmila Tagore]] <br />[[Biswajit Chatterjee]] <br />[[Mumtaz (actress)|Mumtaz]]\n| released          = {{film date|df=yes|1966|05|20}}\n| music         = [[O. P. Nayyar]]\n}}\n'''''Yeh Raat Phir Na Aayegi''''' is a [[Bollywood films of 1966|1966]] Bollywood film starring [[Sharmila Tagore]], [[Biswajit Chatterjee]], [[Prithviraj Kapoor]], [[Mumtaz]] and [[Sailesh Kumar]] in key roles. Mumtaz and Shailesh Kumar played negative roles in this movie.\n\n==Plot==\n''Ye Raat Phir Na Aayegi'' is a rivetting film about a woman's two thousand year old skeleton mysteriously coming to life as Kiran, after it was excavated by Reeta and her assistant Rakesh from a site of archaeological interest. Amid the passage of these surreal events, Reeta and her widower father come to know that Kiran has resurfaced after two thousand years to claim Suraj, her lover from the past life, who is presently engaged to Reeta as her fianc\u00e9.\n\n==Cast==\n\n*[[Biswajit Chatterjee]] as Suraj\n*[[Sharmila Tagore]] as Kiran\n*[[Mumtaz (actress)|Mumtaz]] as Reeta\n*[[Prithviraj Kapoor]] as Professor\n*[[Sailesh Kumar]] as Rakesh\n*[[Helen (actress)|Helen]] as Dancer\n*[[B. M. Vyas]] as Sailor\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Song !! Singer\n|-\n| 1\n| \"Mera Pyaar Woh Hai\"\n| [[Mahendra Kapoor]]\n|-\n| 2\n| \"Huzoorewala Jo Ho Ijaazat\"\n| '''[[Asha Bhosle]]''', [[Minoo Purushottam]]\n|-\n| 3\n| \"Phir Miloge Kabhi Is Baat Ka Vaada Karlo\"\n| '''[[Asha Bhosle]]''', [[Mohammed Rafi]]\n|-\n| 4\n| \"Aap Se Maine Meri Jaan Mohabbat