{"title_page": "IPod Touch (4th generation)", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=October 2015}}\n\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name = iPod Touch\n| logo = [[File:IPodtouchlogo.svg|140px]]\n| image = [[File:4th Generation iPod touch.png|150px]]\n| caption = A black iPod touch (4th generation)\n| developer = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| manufacturer = [[Foxconn]]\n| slogan = \n| family = [[iPod]]\n| type = [[Handheld PC]]\n| releasedate = {{Start date and age|2010|09|01}}\n| lifespan = \n| discontinued = {{end date and age|October 11, 2012}} (8, 64GB)<br/>{{end date and age|May 30, 2013}} (16, 32GB)\n| dimensions = {{convert|110|mm|in|abbr=on}} H <br /> {{convert|58|mm|in|abbr=on}} W <br /> {{convert|7.1|mm|in|abbr=on}} D\n| weight = {{convert|101|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| os = '''Original:''' [[iOS 4#4.1|iOS 4.1]], [[iOS 5]] (White model)<br>'''Last:''' [[iOS 6#6.1.6|iOS 6.1.6]], released {{start date|mf=yes|2014|02|21}}\n| soc = [[Apple A4]]\n| cpu = ARM Cortex-A8 Apple A4 800 MHz\n| storage = 8, 16, 32 or 64&nbsp;[[gigabyte|GB]] [[flash memory]]\t\n| memory = 256&nbsp;[[megabyte|MB]] [[dynamic random-access memory|DRAM]]\n| display = {{convert|3.5|in|mm|abbr=on}} diagonal (3:2 aspect ratio),<br /> multi-touch display,<br /> [[LED backlit]] [[TFT LCD#In-plane switching|IPS TFT LCD]],<br /> 960\u00d7640&nbsp;[[pixel|px]] at 326&nbsp;[[pixels per inch|PPI]]<br /> 800:1 [[contrast ratio]] (typical), 500&nbsp;[[luminance|cd/m<sup>2</sup>]] max. brightness (typical), [[Fingerprint]]-resistant [[Lipophobicity|oleophobic]] [[coating]] on front\n| graphics = PowerVR SGX535 GPU\n| sound =\n| input = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Multi-touch]] [[touchscreen]] display\t\n* Volume buttons\t\n* Microphone\t\n* Built-in speaker\t\n* [[Voice control]]\n* 3-axis [[gyroscope]]\n* 3-axis [[Accelerometer]]\n* Ambient Light Sensor \n}}\n| controllers =\n| camera = {{Plainlist|\n* '''Rear:''' 0.7 [[megapixel|MP]] [[backside illumination|back-side illuminated sensor]]<br/>[[high-definition video|HD video recording]] [[720p]] up to 30 frames/s with audio<br/>[[F-number|Aperture]] f/2.4<br/>[[facial recognition system|Facial recognition]] (stills only)\n* '''Front:''' FaceTime [[high-definition video|HD camera]] with 0.3 [[megapixel|MP]] <br/> VGN up to 30 frames/s with audio\t\n}}\n| touchpad =\n| connectivity = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11n|802.11b/g/n]] (802.11n 2.4 GHz)\t\n* [[Bluetooth 2.1|Bluetooth 2.1 + EDR]]\t\n}}\n| service = [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]], [[iTunes Store]], [[iBookstore]], [[iCloud]], [[Apple Wallet|Passbook]], [[MobileMe]]\n| topgame = \n| compatibility =\t\n| predecessor = [[iPod Touch (3rd generation)]]\n| successor =[[iPod Touch (5th generation)]]\n| website =\n}}\n{{iPod models}}\n\nThe '''iPod touch (4th generation)''' (colloquially known as the '''iPod Touch 4G''' or the '''iPod touch 4''') was the dumbest 4th generation [[iPod Touch]] by [[Apple Inc]]. Released alongside the [[iPhone 4]], it was the first iPod to offer front and rear facing cameras. Like the iPhone 4, it used the [[Apple A4 chip]]. It fully supports [[iOS 4]], and [[iOS 5]], but has limited support for [[iOS 6]] and unlike the [[iPhone 4]], the device did not get [[iOS 7]] due to performance issues. It was only offered in white and black. The white-colored version was added in October 2011. On October 11, 2012, Apple discontinued the 8GB and 64GB models with the release of the 32 and 64GB models of the [[iPod Touch 5]], leaving the 16GB and the 32GB models. They were later discontinued when Apple introduced a 16GB version of its successor, the [[iPod Touch 5]] on May 30, 2013, which was sold at the same price point as the iPod touch 4, but with a larger 4\" retina display and an [[Apple A5|Apple A5 chip]]. On November 14, 2013, Apple issued [[iOS 6|iOS 6.1.5]] for the iPod touch (4th generation) to fix FaceTime calls failing. On February 21, 2014, Apple issued [[iOS 6|iOS 6.1.6]] for the iPod touch (4th generation) and [[iPhone 3GS]] to fix faulty SSL verification.\n\nThe 4th generation model was the last of the iPod Touch players released to use the [[Dock_connector#Mobile_devices|30-pin dock connector]], which was substituted with the [[Lightning (connector)|Lightning]] connector starting with the 5th generation of iPod Touch players.\n\n== History==\nThe iPod touch fourth generation was released on September 12th, 2010. At the time, there was only a black model. Then, in October 12th, 2011, a white model of the iPod Touch was released.\n==In popular culture==\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{compu-mobile-stub}}\n\n{{iOS}}\n{{iPod}}\n{{Apple hardware since 1998}}\n{{Apple}}\n\n[[Category:IPod]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=October 2015}}\n\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name = iPod Touch\n| logo = [[File:IPodtouchlogo.svg|140px]]\n| image = [[File:4th Generation iPod touch.png|150px]]\n| caption = A black iPod touch (4th generation)\n| developer = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| manufacturer = [[Foxconn]]\n| slogan = \n| family = [[iPod]]\n| type = [[Handheld PC]]\n| releasedate = {{Start date and age|2010|09|01}}\n| lifespan = \n| discontinued = {{end date and age|October 11, 2012}} (8, 64GB)<br/>{{end date and age|May 30, 2013}} (16, 32GB)\n| dimensions = {{convert|110|mm|in|abbr=on}} H <br /> {{convert|58|mm|in|abbr=on}} W <br /> {{convert|7.1|mm|in|abbr=on}} D\n| weight = {{convert|101|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| os = '''Original:''' [[iOS 4#4.1|iOS 4.1]], [[iOS 5]] (White model)<br>'''Last:''' [[iOS 6#6.1.6|iOS 6.1.6]], released {{start date|mf=yes|2014|02|21}}\n| soc = [[Apple A4]]\n| cpu = ARM Cortex-A8 Apple A4 800 MHz\n| storage = 8, 16, 32 or 64&nbsp;[[gigabyte|GB]] [[flash memory]]\t\n| memory = 256&nbsp;[[megabyte|MB]] [[dynamic random-access memory|DRAM]]\n| display = {{convert|3.5|in|mm|abbr=on}} diagonal (3:2 aspect ratio),<br /> multi-touch display,<br /> [[LED backlit]] [[TFT LCD#In-plane switching|IPS TFT LCD]],<br /> 960\u00d7640&nbsp;[[pixel|px]] at 326&nbsp;[[pixels per inch|PPI]]<br /> 800:1 [[contrast ratio]] (typical), 500&nbsp;[[luminance|cd/m<sup>2</sup>]] max. brightness (typical), [[Fingerprint]]-resistant [[Lipophobicity|oleophobic]] [[coating]] on front\n| graphics = PowerVR SGX535 GPU\n| sound =\n| input = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Multi-touch]] [[touchscreen]] display\t\n* Volume buttons\t\n* Microphone\t\n* Built-in speaker\t\n* [[Voice control]]\n* 3-axis [[gyroscope]]\n* 3-axis [[Accelerometer]]\n* Ambient Light Sensor \n}}\n| controllers =\n| camera = {{Plainlist|\n* '''Rear:''' 0.7 [[megapixel|MP]] [[backside illumination|back-side illuminated sensor]]<br/>[[high-definition video|HD video recording]] [[720p]] up to 30 frames/s with audio<br/>[[F-number|Aperture]] f/2.4<br/>[[facial recognition system|Facial recognition]] (stills only)\n* '''Front:''' FaceTime [[high-definition video|HD camera]] with 0.3 [[megapixel|MP]] <br/> VGN up to 30 frames/s with audio\t\n}}\n| touchpad =\n| connectivity = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11n|802.11b/g/n]] (802.11n 2.4 GHz)\t\n* [[Bluetooth 2.1|Bluetooth 2.1 + EDR]]\t\n}}\n| service = [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]], [[iTunes Store]], [[iBookstore]], [[iCloud]], [[Apple Wallet|Passbook]], [[MobileMe]]\n| topgame = \n| compatibility =\t\n| predecessor = [[iPod Touch (3rd generation)]]\n| successor =[[iPod Touch (5th generation)]]\n| website =\n}}\n{{iPod models}}\n\nThe '''iPod touch (4th generation)''' (colloquially known as the '''iPod Touch 4G''' or the '''iPod touch 4''') was the 4th generation [[iPod Touch]] by [[Apple Inc]]. Released alongside the [[iPhone 4]], it was the first iPod to offer front and rear facing cameras. Like the iPhone 4, it used the [[Apple A4 chip]]. It fully supports [[iOS 4]], and [[iOS 5]], but has limited support for [[iOS 6]] and unlike the [[iPhone 4]], the device did not get [[iOS 7]] due to performance issues. It was only offered in white and black. The white-colored version was added in October 2011. On October 11, 2012, Apple discontinued the 8GB and 64GB models with the release of the 32 and 64GB models of the [[iPod Touch 5]], leaving the 16GB and the 32GB models. They were later discontinued when Apple introduced a 16GB version of its successor, the [[iPod Touch 5]] on May 30, 2013, which was sold at the same price point as the iPod touch 4, but with a larger 4\" retina display and an [[Apple A5|Apple A5 chip]]. On November 14, 2013, Apple issued [[iOS 6|iOS 6.1.5]] for the iPod touch (4th generation) to fix FaceTime calls failing. On February 21, 2014, Apple issued [[iOS 6|iOS 6.1.6]] for the iPod touch (4th generation) and [[iPhone 3GS]] to fix faulty SSL verification.\n\nThe 4th generation model was the last of the iPod Touch players released to use the [[Dock_connector#Mobile_devices|30-pin dock connector]], which was substituted with the [[Lightning (connector)|Lightning]] connector starting with the 5th generation of iPod Touch players.\n\n== History==\nThe iPod touch fourth generation was released on September 12th, 2010. At the time, there was only a black model. Then, in October 12th, 2011, a white model of the iPod Touch was released.\n==In popular culture==\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{compu-mobile-stub}}\n\n{{iOS}}\n{{iPod}}\n{{Apple hardware since 1998}}\n{{Apple}}\n\n[[Category:IPod]]\n", "name_user": "2606:a000:1014:8ac7:5d02:b3de:d87b:233e", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPod_Touch_(4th_generation)"}
